{
  "stem": "24515.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he didn't dare tell us, until somebody, a friend of my father, said he would, if he didn't.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we found out that Father was gone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then a year, or two later-- you see, now we knew that things were strange-- they left [INAUDIBLE], our old address, the apartment, they had gone to somewhere else, which we imagine was a Jewish ghetto-type thing-- a house.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then after Father's death, Mother went to Berlin to a certain place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then she, very carefully, wrote a letter to the lady-- this marvelous lady, who looked after my brother and me, most beautiful person-- to say that she was moving her-- her-- her place of-- of living-- of-- living place, which we knew exactly what it meant.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The lady saw the Red Cross letter and very happily gave it to my brother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he got full in the face to see that his mother was being sent East.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And for years we didn't know what had happened to her, but relatively recently-- a book of names, and so on, that she was shot in Riga.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, by-- by one of the transports, the transports East.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "An earlier booklet tells us that she went on such and such transport, East, East Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But apparently didn't go to Auschwitz, went to Riga, apparently.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When-- when the war was over-- I'm staying with your parents-- when-- when the war was over--",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Forgive me, when I was staying with my parents?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Did you say when I was staying with my parents?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When the war was over, in 1945-- Yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, yes, of course.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew what had happened to my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, that was the registry, the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother had said for years, we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
